{
  "stem": "14897.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the room next to us was a kind of a-- a-- a-- an exterminating room, where people would be crowded, like 800 to 1,000, literally stacked one on top of the other, locked up.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The windows would be locked up, and they would be sort of suffocating in there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we would hear the cries during the night in every European language of people in extremis.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in the morning-- and they would put a few kapos in there to-- to beat them and stomp, and people would panic.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There wouldn't be enough air, and they would literally kick each other and-- and stomp on each other.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they would bring out the bodies in the morning, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So even though there were no gas chambers, there were terrible things going on in Bergen-Belsen also-- Bergen-Belsen, you know, the place where Anne Frank died.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was in a-- in a-- in a group next to ours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I never met her, but we knew there were Dutch and Hungarian Jews in the next group next to us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew from the papers and so on that-- that the war, the Germans were losing the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We could not visualize how we would survive the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The way it-- it finally happened is that one day, the Germans showed up, again with their dogs, and took us to the same siding.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had to march several kilometers to the siding, a group of 5,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they told us that we were being transferred to Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We knew that Bergen-Belsen was in the path of the British troops.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was now in April of 1945.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they put us on a train, 5,000 of us.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
